  "DSPVersions": [],
  "overview": "A pipeline of multiple Batch Executables is built to migrate Salesforce Files (for a particular object identified by the FirstPublishLocationId field) and their associated links to a remote org. The process begins by migrating ContentVersion data while storing the source identifiers in custom fields, followed by migrating ContentDocumentLink to re-establish the links. Additional batches apply the same pattern to other linked objects.",
  "generalUseCase": "Use a Pipeline with sequential #Batch Executables to migrate Salesforce Files and rebuild their links in a target org, using VLOOKUP and External IDs to maintain data relationships when re-establishing ContentDocumentLink associations.",
